are a group of genetic conditions characterised by progressive muscle weakness and degeneration. They vary in terms of age of onset, severity, and the specific muscles affected. The most common is \u003Cstrong\u003EDuchenne muscular dystrophy \u003C/strong\u003Ewhich is an X-linked recessive disorder. Dystrophin gene mutations result in fewer functional dystrophin proteins. This results in progressive muscle degeneration and weakness, primarily affecting boys. The other types of muscular dystrophy, such as \u003Cstrong\u003EFacioscapulohumeral muscular dystrophy\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003EBecker muscular dystrophy\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003EMyotonic muscular dystrophy\u003C/strong\u003E, and \u003Cstrong\u003ELimb-girdle muscular dystrophy\u003C/strong\u003E, are less common and have different genetic causes and clinical presentations.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Duchenne muscular dystrophy is caused by mutations in the dystrophin gene located on the X chromosome. It is the most common muscular dystrophy","Duchenne muscular dystrophy primarily affects boys and leads to progressive muscle weakness."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","Longo, U. G., \u0026 Denaro, V. (Eds.). (2023). Textbook of musculoskeletal disorders. Springer Nature","Hughes, S. H. (2022). The Musculoskeletal System: The Musculoskeletal System-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Frontera WR, Ochala J. Skeletal muscle: a brief review of structure and function. Calcif Tissue Int. 2015 Mar;96(3):183-95. doi: 10.1007/s00223-014-9915-y. Epub 2014 Oct 8. PMID: 25294644","Morrison BM. Neuromuscular Diseases. Semin Neurol. 2016 Oct;36(5):409-418. doi: 10.1